summary: Robert Baratheon last wish was to revoke the death order against Dany. He repented. He didn't want her to die and cursed Renly...
question: Robert Baratheon last wish was to revoke the death order against Dany. He repented. He didn't want her to die and cursed Renly and the others. Why you refuse to accept that he could have want her as his heir? Cersei and Jon are true betrayals against him, while Dany is his only family left after all. I'm really curious to know. Thanks.
answer: Anon, Robert won that throne by conquest removing the Targaryen claim. He agreed with Ned on his deathbed that sending assassins after a pregnant teenager was morally wrong. He didn’t know that Cersei passed Jaime’s children as his own and even if he did, Stannis would be his heir. Now Dany could use the fact that she is Robert’s cousin to bolster her claim to the Iron Throne but at this point she hates him and thinks RR was illegal so I doubt she will

summary: i have to say i find it kind of ironic that someone would be surprised that you’re african based on your love for the martells...
question: i have to say i find it kind of ironic that someone would be surprised that you’re african based on your love for the martells considering you know, they are based on the moors, who are african. i guess african headcanons just aren’t as populair? and there is a sore lack of africans in the fandom so it’s really cool to see another one be so populair!
answer:
The usual fancast for Martells are South East Asians and many Martell stans are Asian so I understand where anon’s assumptions came from. But yeah North African headcanons aren’t widespread at all which is a shame since Alexander Siddig is part Sudanese.

Also thank you. Feel free to message me if you want
